class.name: uk.co.martinpearman.b4a.touchimageview.TouchImageViewWrapper
class.event: Click(X As Int, Y As Int)
LongClick(X As Int, Y As Int)

method.name: PostTranslate
method.comment: Move the image by X, Y pixels.

method.name: GetDestRect
method.comment: Returns a Rect that describes the current scale and position of the image within the TouchImageView.

method.name: ScaleSrcRectToDestRect
method.comment: Scale and position the area of the (foreground) image defined by SrcRect to the area of the TouchImageView defined by DestRect. ScaleToFit controls how the image should be aligned in the DestRect: CENTER - Center and maximise the image to fit the DestRect maintaining the aspect ratio. END - Maximise the image to fit the DestRect maintaining the aspect ratio, align the image with the bottom and right edges of the DestRect. FILL - Maximise the image to completely fill the DestRect, the aspect ratio may not be maintained. START - Maximise the image to fit the DestRect maintaining the aspect ratio, align the image with the top and left edges of the DestRect.

method.name: PreScale
method.comment: Change the current image scale by Scale, centering the change on (X, Y).

method.name: CreateLog
method.comment: Creates log entries with details about the current state of the TouchImageView.

property.name: MinScale
property.comment: Get or set the minimum scale that the image can be reduced by (zoomed out). Default MinScale is 0.5.

property.name: Gravity
property.comment: Get or Set the Gravity of the BackgroundImage.

property.name: TransformedBitmap
property.comment: Get the transformed image as a Bitmap.

property.name: TranslatePaddingX
property.comment: Get or set the minimum number of pixels that the image will always display within the TouchImageView. Default TranslatePadding is 64 pixels. The image can not be dragged out of visibility, at least 64 pixels of width and height will always be visible.

property.name: ClickPeriod
property.comment: Get or Set the ClickPeriod in milliseconds. The ClickPeriod is the threshold between a click being treated as a Click or a LongClick. The default ClickPeriod is 200 milliseconds.

property.name: TouchEnabled
property.comment: Get or Set whether touch events are enabled.

property.name: MaxScale
property.comment: Get or set the maximum scale that the image can be enlarged by (zoomed in). Default MaxScale is 1.5.

property.name: ScaleX
property.comment: Get the factor which the image is currently scaled by on it's X axis.

property.name: ScaleY
property.comment: Get the factor which the image is currently scaled by on it's Y axis.
